General Assembly Proposed Bill No. 5189
February Session, 2026 LCO No. 994
Referred to Committee on FINANCE, REVENUE AND
BONDING
Introduced by:
REP. WILSON, 46th Dist.
SEN. OSTEN, 19th Dist.
REP. PEMBERTON, 139th Dist.
AN ACT AUTHORIZING BONDS OF THE STATE FOR THE HOLY
TRINITY GREEK ORTHODOX CHURCH IN THE CITY OF NORWICH.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General
Assembly convened:
1 That the State Bond Commission be empowered to authorize the
2 issuance of bonds of the state in accordance with section 3-20 of the
3 general statutes, in principal amounts not exceeding in the aggregate
4 five hundred thousand dollars, the proceeds of which shall be used by
5 the Department of Economic and Community Development for the
6 purpose of providing a grant-in-aid to the Holy Trinity Greek Orthodox
7 Church in the city of Norwich for capital improvements.
Statement of Purpose:
To provide funding for capital improvements to the Holy Trinity Greek
Orthodox Church in the city of Norwich.
